76
00:03:42.124 --> 00:03:43.391
If you're into that.

77
00:03:47.596 --> 00:03:48.729
Wow.

78
00:03:48.762 --> 00:03:50.764
NINA: It's basically
Andrew's man cave.

79
00:03:50.798 --> 00:03:54.402
but you are welcome to use it
anytime you want. of course.

80
00:03:54.436 --> 00:03:55.669
You'd be part of the family.

81
00:03:55.703 --> 00:03:57.705
which also means
that you would definitely have

82
00:03:57.738 --> 00:03:59.174
to listen to his TED Talk

83
00:03:59.207 --> 00:04:03.378
about how <i>Barry Lyndon</i> is
a misunderstood masterpiece.

84
00:04:05.646 --> 00:04:07.681
This is the upper living room.

85
00:04:07.715 --> 00:04:10.185
which we barely ever use.
to be honest.

86
00:04:10.218 --> 00:04:12.720
You sure you even need
a housekeeper?

87
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:15.524
Well. actually.
I'm... expecting.

88
00:04:15.557 --> 00:04:17.592
So I'm not gonna have
quite so much time

89
00:04:17.626 --> 00:04:19.561
to keep everything so perfect.

90
00:04:19.594 --> 00:04:22.330
But don't tell Andrew
because it's very early

91
00:04:22.364 --> 00:04:25.600
and I want to be sure.
you know. before I tell him.

92
00:04:25.634 --> 00:04:27.202
Yeah. Congrats.

93
00:04:27.235 --> 00:04:28.303
Thank you.

94
00:04:29.404 --> 00:04:31.239
This is Cece's room.

95
00:04:31.273 --> 00:04:32.240
Andrew even made a little

96
00:04:32.274 --> 00:04:34.808
miniature version
of our house for her.

97
00:04:34.842 --> 00:04:36.311
-Isn't that sweet?
-Wow.

98
00:04:42.584 --> 00:04:44.718
NINA: So the laundry room is
in the basement.

99
00:04:44.752 --> 00:04:47.489
and that would be
your bathroom

100
00:04:47.522 --> 00:04:49.723
and you would be upstairs.

101
00:04:51.226 --> 00:04:53.295
You're gonna think
it's a little bit small.

102
00:04:53.328 --> 00:04:55.263
but it's got a lot of privacy.

103
00:04:55.297 --> 00:04:57.532
and we figured that that was
the most important thing.

104
00:04:57.566 --> 00:04:59.634
Lots of light. though.

105
00:04:59.668 --> 00:05:00.868
Ta-da!

106
00:05:00.902 --> 00:05:02.770
You can make it your own.
of course.

107
00:05:02.803 --> 00:05:05.173
You can hang posters
and bring in potted plants.

108
00:05:05.207 --> 00:05:07.075
You can blast your music
as loud as you want

109
00:05:07.108 --> 00:05:09.843
because we cannot
hear you downstairs.

110
00:05:09.877 --> 00:05:11.146
What do you think?

111
00:05:12.713 --> 00:05:14.349
-It's perfect.
-Okay. good.

112
00:05:15.550 --> 00:05:16.884
Win!

113
00:05:16.918 --> 00:05:18.520
Well. I'm still interviewing.

114
00:05:18.553 --> 00:05:20.989
but I'm hoping
to make a decision soon.

115
00:05:22.057 --> 00:05:23.458
Here you go.

116
00:05:23.491 --> 00:05:24.526
Oh. no. you don't
have to do that.

117
00:05:24.559 --> 00:05:25.660
Oh. no. I insist.

118
00:05:25.694 --> 00:05:26.827
You spent your energy
and your time

119
00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:28.463
