to be here. Please.

120
00:05:29.531 --> 00:05:30.932
I appreciate it.

121
00:05:30.966 --> 00:05:34.369
I have a really good feeling
about this. Millie. I do.

122
00:05:34.402 --> 00:05:35.937
Me too.

123
00:05:35.971 --> 00:05:37.539
Okay. I'll be in touch.

124
00:05:37.572 --> 00:05:38.839
(INAUDIBLE)

125
00:05:38.872 --> 00:05:40.208
MILLIE: <i>She won't be in touch.</i>

126
00:05:40.242 --> 00:05:43.411
<i>That's the last time I'll ever</i>
<i>set foot in that house.</i>

127
00:05:43.445 --> 00:05:44.878
<i>One background check.</i>

128
00:05:44.913 --> 00:05:47.983
<i>and she'll see that everything</i>
<i>on that resume is a total lie.</i>

129
00:05:48.016 --> 00:05:49.817
<i>I don't even wear glasses.</i>

130
00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:51.785
<i>I'm just...</i>
<i>I'm trying to look legit.</i>

131
00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:53.088
<i>So stupid.</i>

132
00:05:59.827 --> 00:06:01.396
(HAND DRYER BLOWING)

133
00:06:07.636 --> 00:06:09.337
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

134
00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:13.642
Um. can I get
a job application?

135
00:06:13.675 --> 00:06:15.343
Yeah. sure.

136
00:06:15.377 --> 00:06:17.078
-There you go.
-Thanks.

137
00:06:25.687 --> 00:06:26.921
(HAND DRYER BLOWING)

138
00:06:27.756 --> 00:06:29.391
MILLIE: <i>I knew</i>
<i>she wouldn't call.</i>

139
00:06:29.424 --> 00:06:31.326
<i>Why did I even think I had</i>
<i>a shot at that job?</i>

140
00:06:31.359 --> 00:06:34.362
<i>Oh. well. at least I got</i>
<i>$20 out of it.</i>

141
00:06:35.964 --> 00:06:38.133
(SIGHS) <i>I don't know</i>
<i>what I'm gonna do.</i>

142
00:06:48.310 --> 00:06:49.344
Roll it down.

143
00:06:51.780 --> 00:06:53.281
Can't sleep here.

144
00:06:53.315 --> 00:06:55.016
I'm so sorry. I...

145
00:06:55.050 --> 00:06:56.618
I was driving
from my mom's house

146
00:06:56.651 --> 00:06:57.986
and I got really sleepy.

147
00:06:58.019 --> 00:06:59.721
and I just I pulled over
to take a nap. I'm sorry.

148
00:06:59.754 --> 00:07:02.190
(PHONE VIBRATING)

149
00:07:02.223 --> 00:07:03.925
This is her actually.
Do you mind if I take it?

150
00:07:03.958 --> 00:07:05.293
She's probably freaking out.

151
00:07:05.327 --> 00:07:06.795
Don't text and drive.

152
00:07:06.827 --> 00:07:08.263
I won't. I promise.

153
00:07:11.433 --> 00:07:13.935
-Hello?
<i>-Hi. may I speak to Millie?</i>

154
00:07:13.968 --> 00:07:16.604
Uh. this is her. She.

155
00:07:16.638 --> 00:07:18.373
<i>This is Nina Winchester.</i>

156
00:07:18.406 --> 00:07:20.375
<i>I'm calling</i>
<i>to offer you the job.</i>

157
00:07:20.408 --> 00:07:23.011
<i>I mean. if you're</i>
<i>still available.</i>

158
00:07:23.044 --> 00:07:24.979
<i>Uh. you've probably got</i>
<i>a million job offers.</i>

159
00:07:25.013 --> 00:07:27.048
No. I mean. yes. yes.
I would love to.

160
00:07:27.082 --> 00:07:29.250
Uh. when would
you like me to start?

161
00:07:29.284 --> 00:07:32.987
<i>Oh. my goodness.</i> (SIGHS)
<i>As soon as possible?</i>

162
00:07:33.021 --> 00:07:34.456
Well. what about
this afternoon?

163
00:07:34.489 --> 00:07:35.690
<i>You know what?</i>

164
00:07:35.724 --> 00:07:37.292
<i>-That would be great.</i>
-Great.

165
00:07:37.325 --> 00:07:39.127
<i>Anyway. gotta run.</i>
<i>Bye. Millie.</i>

166
00:07:39.661 --> 00:07:41.029
MILLIE: (SOFTLY) Yes!

167
00:07:49.904 --> 00:07:52.507
-(CLICK)
-(LINE RINGING)

168
00:07:55.076 --> 00:07:56.144
Hey!

169
00:07:57.645 --> 00:07:58.747
-Hey. I'm Millie.
-(LINE RINGING)

170
00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:01.282
Do you work
for the Winchesters?

171
00:08:01.316 --> 00:08:03.818
I'm trying to get in.
but I don't know the code.

172
00:08:03.852 --> 00:08:04.885
(LINE BEEPS)

173
00:08:04.919 --> 00:08:06.154
(GATES CLANK)

174
00:08:30.145 --> 00:08:31.179
Nina?

175
00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.482
Nina. it's Millie.

176
00:08:40.422 --> 00:08:41.456
Nina?

177
00:08:50.498 --> 00:08:52.600
NINA: Millie?
Millie. Millie. Millie!

178
00:08:53.435 --> 00:08:54.803
(EXCLAIMS) Welcome. Hi.

179
00:08:54.836 --> 00:08:56.738
Sorry. I. um. meant
to leave the gate open.

180
00:08:56.771 --> 00:08:59.674
Do you need me to help you bring
in your stuff from your car?

181
00:08:59.707 --> 00:09:01.009
Oh. no. this is it.

182
00:09:01.042 --> 00:09:03.178
-Great. Wow.
-Yeah.

183
00:09:03.211 --> 00:09:04.846
Yeah. no. I put the rest of it
in a storage unit.

184
00:09:04.879 --> 00:09:07.282
Okay. well. that's great. I'm
gonna put these up in your room.

185
00:09:07.315 --> 00:09:10.185
Listen. I need
to write a PTA speech

186
00:09:10.218 --> 00:09:12.287
that has to be a barn burner.

187
00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:13.755
so I'm gonna be
stuck in my office.

188
00:09:13.788 --> 00:09:15.990
But the cleaning supplies are
in this closet over there.

189
00:09:16.424 --> 00:09:18.660
and... um. oh.

190
00:09:18.693 --> 00:09:20.662
You're not wearing
your glasses.

191
00:09:20.695 --> 00:09:23.731
Oh. I don't... I don't wear 'em
all the time. Contacts.

192
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:26.501
Oh.

193
00:09:26.534 --> 00:09:28.369
Yeah. you look better
without them.

194
00:09:29.304 --> 00:09:30.472
Yeah. Okay.

195
00:09:30.972 --> 00:09:33.074
I'll be upstairs.

196
00:09:33.107 --> 00:09:34.576
This is gonna be fun. Millie!

197
00:09:34.609 --> 00:09:36.611
(TUMBLING DICE BY
LINDA RONSTADT PLAYING)

198
00:09:40.648 --> 00:09:45.019
♪ <i>People try to rape me</i>
<i>Always think I'm crazy</i> ♪

199
00:09:45.053 --> 00:09:48.690
♪ <i>Make me burn</i>
<i>the candle right down</i> ♪

200
00:09:49.925 --> 00:09:51.826
♪ <i>Baby</i> ♪

201
00:09:51.860 --> 00:09:53.929
(SONG CONTINUES PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES)

202
00:09:53.963 --> 00:09:55.697
No shoes on the furniture.

203
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.003
Um. hey. Hi.

204
00:10:02.036 --> 00:10:04.772
You must be... Cece.

205
00:10:05.440 --> 00:10:06.674
I'm Millie.

206
00:10:07.475 --> 00:10:08.510
Hello.

207
00:10:09.244 --> 00:10:11.579
Oh. hey. Hi! You met Millie.

208
00:10:11.613 --> 00:10:12.447
Hi. baby.

209
00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:14.549
Millie's gonna be
living with us.

210
00:10:14.582 --> 00:10:15.416
and she's gonna be helping

211
00:10:15.450 --> 00:10:16.751
with the cooking
and the cleaning.

212
00:10:16.784 --> 00:10:17.987
And you know what?

213
00:10:18.052 --> 00:10:19.521
She might even play
<i>Candy Land</i> with you

214
00:10:19.554 --> 00:10:21.789
if you ask her
with a pretty please.

215
00:10:21.823 --> 00:10:23.291
She's gonna live with us?

216
00:10:23.324 --> 00:10:25.727
(LAUGHING) Yes.
Andrew. I told you that.

217
00:10:25.760 --> 00:10:29.932
I said she was gonna be living
in the guest room in the attic.

218
00:10:29.965 --> 00:10:32.433
Doesn't this place look
incredible. Look at it.

219
00:10:35.069 --> 00:10:37.672
-Thank you.
-Well. Millie. welcome.

220
00:10:37.705 --> 00:10:39.073
Uh. thank you.

221
00:10:39.107 --> 00:10:40.408
Are you hungry?
I'm sure we can

222
00:10:40.441 --> 00:10:42.011
turn this dinner for three
into a dinner for four.

223
00:10:42.043 --> 00:10:44.112
No. I'm probably
just gonna go upstairs

224
00:10:44.145 --> 00:10:46.447
and. uh. get all settled in.

225
00:10:46.481 --> 00:10:47.682
-You sure?
-If you don't mind.

226
00:10:47.715 --> 00:10:50.251
I'll just come down afterwards
and tidy up.

227
00:10:50.285 --> 00:10:52.420
Yeah. get settled.
Yeah. take your time.

228
00:10:52.453 --> 00:10:53.923
We're so happy
that you're here.

229
00:10:53.956 --> 00:10:55.557
You just let us know
if you change your mind.

230
00:10:56.491 --> 00:10:57.559
Thanks.

231
00:11:02.764 --> 00:11:04.832
You ordered from the wrong
Italian place again.

232
00:11:41.036 --> 00:11:42.270
NINA: Knock. knock.

233
00:11:43.638 --> 00:11:44.472
Hi.

234
00:11:44.505 --> 00:11:46.674
That window doesn't open. sadly.

235
00:11:46.708 --> 00:11:48.576
But there's a lot
of ventilation in this room.

236
00:11:48.610 --> 00:11:50.612
so you should never
get stuffy in here.

237
00:11:50.645 --> 00:11:51.981
I got you some dinner.

238
00:11:52.014 --> 00:11:54.682
Andrew always over-orders.

239
00:11:54.716 --> 00:11:55.650
I put some water

240
00:11:55.683 --> 00:11:57.019
in the mini fridge.
did you see that?

241
00:11:57.052 --> 00:11:58.686
Yeah. I really don't
want to be a pain.

242
00:11:58.720 --> 00:12:01.422
but if it is possible to try
and get the window open.

243
00:12:01.456 --> 00:12:03.591
it'd be nice to get
some fresh air in here.

244
00:12:03.625 --> 00:12:06.127
Yeah. I agree.
That's a great idea.

245
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:07.895
I will talk to the handyman
about that.

246
00:12:07.930 --> 00:12:10.598
Okay. cool. Is that the guy
that's down in the yard?

247
00:12:10.632 --> 00:12:12.800
No. that's Enzo.
He's the groundskeeper.

248
00:12:12.834 --> 00:12:14.168
Never mind him.

249
00:12:14.202 --> 00:12:16.204
And then if I could just
get a key for the deadbolt.

250
00:12:16.237 --> 00:12:19.173
Oh. my God. yes. The deadbolt.

251
00:12:19.207 --> 00:12:22.011
(CHUCKLES) That's so creepy.

252
00:12:22.044 --> 00:12:25.847
This used to be Andrew's storage
closet for his files. Okay?

253
00:12:25.880 --> 00:12:27.315
But. oh. my God.

254
00:12:27.815 --> 00:12:29.717
closed window. deadbolt.

255
00:12:31.386 --> 00:12:33.022
What kind of monsters are we?

256
00:12:33.055 --> 00:12:34.889
-Uh...
-I will sort that out.

257
00:12:34.923 --> 00:12:36.591
Oh. before I forget. Um...

258
00:12:38.192 --> 00:12:39.827
This is for you. A present.

259
00:12:39.861 --> 00:12:42.931
Also. just. I saw that your
phone was just really ancient.

260
00:12:42.965 --> 00:12:45.199
and I wanted you to have that

261
00:12:45.233 --> 00:12:48.070
because I uploaded
the credit card onto it

262
00:12:48.103 --> 00:12:49.138
so you can use it
at the grocery store

263
00:12:49.170 --> 00:12:50.438
and for gas.

264
00:12:50.471 --> 00:12:52.874
Oh. um. I'll take good care
of it. Thank you.

265
00:12:52.908 --> 00:12:58.279
Honestly. I'm like. so happy
that... you're here with us.

266
00:12:58.947 --> 00:13:00.314
Thanks.

267
00:13:00.348 --> 00:13:01.883
Can I give you a hug?

268
00:13:03.851 --> 00:13:05.720
(SIGHS) Thank you. Millie.

269
00:13:05.753 --> 00:13:07.722
Thank you. Okay.

270
00:13:07.755 --> 00:13:09.590
Let me know
if you need anything else.

271
00:13:27.208 --> 00:13:28.609
(YAWNS)

272
00:13:34.917 --> 00:13:35.951
Shit.

273
00:13:44.193 --> 00:13:45.426
(CLICKS)

274
00:13:45.928 --> 00:13:48.629
(LOCK RATTLES)

275
00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:49.497
No. no. no.

276
00:13:49.530 --> 00:13:51.934
-(STRAINING)
-(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

277
00:13:51.967 --> 00:13:53.334
No. no. no.

278
00:13:53.835 --> 00:13:55.336
(DOOR CREAKS)

279
00:13:58.239 --> 00:13:59.474
(SHRIEKING)

280
00:14:06.949 --> 00:14:08.449
Nina?

281
00:14:08.483 --> 00:14:10.418
-(SHOUTING) Where are they?
-Where are what?

282
00:14:10.451 --> 00:14:12.620
My PTA notes
for the meeting tonight!

283
00:14:12.653 --> 00:14:14.089
They were right here
on the counter.

284
00:14:14.123 --> 00:14:15.224
and now they're not here.

285
00:14:15.256 --> 00:14:16.657
-Where are they?
-I didn't see any notes.

286
00:14:16.691 --> 00:14:17.926
Bullshit!

287
00:14:17.960 --> 00:14:18.994
Where are they?

288
00:14:20.229 --> 00:14:21.997
-Nina. no. no.
-ANDREW: Hey.

289
00:14:22.030 --> 00:14:23.331
Hey! What's going on?

290
00:14:23.364 --> 00:14:27.035
Millie threw away my notes
for the meeting tonight.

291
00:14:28.569 --> 00:14:30.471
(SHOUTING) Where are they?

292
00:14:32.273 --> 00:14:34.209
Nina. why don't we go
check your office?

293
00:14:34.243 --> 00:14:36.111
I have to get up
and do a speech

294
00:14:36.145 --> 00:14:37.345
in front of everybody

295
00:14:37.378 --> 00:14:38.679
and now I have nothing!

296
00:14:38.713 --> 00:14:41.150
-(OBJECTS CLATTERING)
-(SHRIEKING)

297
00:14:41.183 --> 00:14:42.951
-ANDREW: Nina!
-(YELLING) What?

298
00:14:42.985 --> 00:14:45.220
-(DRAWER SLIDING SHUT)
-(THUDS)

299
00:14:45.254 --> 00:14:47.455
-Do you have a copy...
-(VESSELS CLINKING)

300
00:14:48.023 --> 00:14:49.258
...on your computer?

301
00:14:49.290 --> 00:14:51.392
I wrote them by hand!

302
00:14:51.927 --> 00:14:53.561
Oh. fuck!

303
00:14:53.594 --> 00:14:55.897
I always think better
when I write by hand.

304
00:14:55.931 --> 00:14:57.465
Where's my nail at?

305
00:14:58.066 --> 00:14:59.634
(SHRIEKS AND WHIMPERS)

306
00:15:00.202 --> 00:15:04.539
(CRYING)

307
00:15:04.572 --> 00:15:06.175
ANDREW: All right.
Come here. come here.

308
00:15:06.208 --> 00:15:08.342
-(CRYING)
-It's okay.

309
00:15:09.811 --> 00:15:13.182
(CRYING)

310
00:15:13.215 --> 00:15:15.449
ANDREW: Let's take
a deep breath. okay?

311
00:15:15.483 --> 00:15:17.718
-(NINA CONTINUES CRYING)
-Breathe. breathe. breathe.

312
00:15:17.752 --> 00:15:20.189
-Breathe. breathe. breathe.
-(SNIFFLES)

313
00:15:20.222 --> 00:15:22.423
(EXHALES AND SNIFFLES)

314
00:15:23.025 --> 00:15:24.325
I'm gonna pick you up.

315
00:15:27.395 --> 00:15:28.696
-(NINA CRIES)
-(ANDREW GRUNTS SOFTLY)

316
00:15:28.729 --> 00:15:30.966
(NINA SOBBING)

317
00:15:35.037 --> 00:15:38.040
Here's the plan. I am going
to take Cece to school.

318
00:15:38.073 --> 00:15:39.774
and you...

319
00:15:39.807 --> 00:15:42.211
you are going to take
a hot shower.

320
00:15:42.244 --> 00:15:43.744
You're gonna have
a nice long breakfast.

321
00:15:43.778 --> 00:15:45.680
and then you have all day
to work on your speech.

322
00:15:45.713 --> 00:15:48.984
and you can still make it
to the salon for a touch up.

323
00:15:49.017 --> 00:15:50.953
You'll have just enough time
to get your roots done.

324
00:15:50.986 --> 00:15:52.187
I love you so much.

325
00:15:52.221 --> 00:15:53.588
-I love you.
-I love you.

326
00:15:56.657 --> 00:15:58.927
You need to be
more careful next time.

327
00:16:01.029 --> 00:16:02.697
You've ruined my entire day.

328
00:16:04.365 --> 00:16:05.600
I'm sorry.

329
00:16:10.805 --> 00:16:12.040
(ANDREW SIGHS)

330
00:16:14.442 --> 00:16:15.676
I am so sorry.

331
00:16:16.979 --> 00:16:18.080
Don-- Don't worry about it.

332
00:16:18.113 --> 00:16:19.814
I don't know what's been
going on with her lately.

333
00:16:19.847 --> 00:16:21.449
She's...

334
00:16:21.482 --> 00:16:24.119
she's been on a real
emotional roller coaster.

335
00:16:24.152 --> 00:16:25.887
Oh. it's probably the hor--

336
00:16:27.289 --> 00:16:29.490
um. Mercury in retrograde.

337
00:16:29.523 --> 00:16:31.360
Didn't peg you
for the star-chart type.

338
00:16:31.392 --> 00:16:32.793
Guilty.

339
00:16:36.031 --> 00:16:37.598
Let me help you clean up.

340
00:16:37.632 --> 00:16:39.167
-It's a fuckin' mess in here.
-No. no. no. I got it.

341
00:16:39.201 --> 00:16:41.303
I got it. You go get ready.

342
00:16:41.336 --> 00:16:42.837
I don't want you
to be late for Cece.

343
00:16:43.939 --> 00:16:45.040
Thank you.

344
00:16:47.976 --> 00:16:50.611
-(TAPS COUNTERTOP)
-Tomorrow will be better.

345
00:16:52.613 --> 00:16:54.582
It'll be better. I promise.

346
00:16:55.150 --> 00:16:56.184
Okay.

347
00:17:01.689 --> 00:17:03.258
-Yeah.
-(TAPS COUNTERTOP)

348
00:17:03.292 --> 00:17:05.660
Cece! Let's hit the road!

349
00:17:07.129 --> 00:17:08.931
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS)

350
00:17:25.914 --> 00:17:27.515
(IN NON-NATIVE ACCENT)
What are you doing here?

351
00:17:28.116 --> 00:17:29.483
I work here.

352
00:17:30.419 --> 00:17:32.087
What are you doing here?

353
00:17:32.988 --> 00:17:34.522
You...

354
00:17:42.530 --> 00:17:46.500
(MUTTERS IN ITALIAN)

355
00:18:02.650 --> 00:18:04.119
-(YAWNS)
-(BUCKET THUDS)

356
00:18:09.291 --> 00:18:12.094
(EERIE MUSIC PLAYING)

357
00:18:24.739 --> 00:18:26.475
I don't really
fit in very well

358
00:18:26.507 --> 00:18:28.542
with those other PTA moms.

359
00:18:29.777 --> 00:18:32.447
I guess I didn't realize
how stressed I've been.

360
00:18:32.481 --> 00:18:36.084
It's probably just all the new
hormones making you go crazy.

361
00:18:38.753 --> 00:18:40.422
I wouldn't say anything
to Andrew.

362
00:18:40.455 --> 00:18:41.789
Get out.

363
00:18:42.324 --> 00:18:43.458
I have to shower.

364
00:18:43.492 --> 00:18:45.327
And you're gonna
handle dinner later.

365
00:18:45.360 --> 00:18:46.594
MILLIE: Yeah.

366
00:18:47.362 --> 00:18:48.497
ANDREW: It smells amazing.

367
00:18:48.529 --> 00:18:50.332
MILLIE: It's chicken piccata.

368
00:18:50.365 --> 00:18:51.599
ANDREW: Mmm.

369
00:18:51.632 --> 00:18:53.834
Oh. I picked this up for Cece.

370
00:18:53.868 --> 00:18:56.804
Oh. these are fantastic.
She's gonna love these.

371
00:18:56.837 --> 00:18:58.040
Someone did not
get her snack today.

372
00:18:58.073 --> 00:19:00.442
and she's a very hungry
little ballerina.

373
00:19:00.475 --> 00:19:01.943
(MILLIE CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

374
00:19:01.977 --> 00:19:04.413
Why don't you get her started.
and I'll be right back down?

375
00:19:04.446 --> 00:19:05.846
Okay.

376
00:19:08.350 --> 00:19:09.650
(SIGHS)

377
00:19:11.585 --> 00:19:13.021
Hey. Cece.

378
00:19:13.388 --> 00:19:14.722
how was class?

379
00:19:16.258 --> 00:19:17.426
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

380
00:19:17.459 --> 00:19:20.861
Would you. uh. like juice
or... or water?

381
00:19:20.895 --> 00:19:23.631
Juice.
But this glass is dirty.

382
00:19:24.565 --> 00:19:26.334
Really? I just took it out
of the dishwasher.

383
00:19:26.368 --> 00:19:27.635
Juice is a privilege.

384
00:19:27.668 --> 00:19:30.105
Not something you drink
out of a dirty glass.

385
00:19:31.540 --> 00:19:32.807
Of course not.

386
00:19:34.109 --> 00:19:35.143
(SIGHS)

387
00:19:46.254 --> 00:19:47.989
This looks amazing.

388
00:19:48.023 --> 00:19:50.926
Doesn't it. Cece? Way better
than dinosaur nuggets.

389
00:19:52.626 --> 00:19:54.162
Hey. Millie.

390
00:19:54.196 --> 00:19:57.065
why don't you grab
a place setting and join us?

391
00:19:58.066 --> 00:19:59.101
Uh...

392
00:19:59.134 --> 00:20:00.569
No. I... I already ate.

393
00:20:00.601 --> 00:20:01.869
Oh. we insist.

394
00:20:02.703 --> 00:20:04.172
Don't we. Cece?

395
00:20:06.441 --> 00:20:07.675
Um...

396
00:20:08.709 --> 00:20:10.345
I hope you guys like it.

397
00:20:30.332 --> 00:20:31.933
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

398
00:20:33.101 --> 00:20:34.236
Come in.

399
00:20:36.605 --> 00:20:38.607
Hey.

400
00:20:38.639 --> 00:20:40.808
-Hey.
-Sorry to bother you.

401
00:20:42.310 --> 00:20:43.644
Got something for you.

402
00:20:43.677 --> 00:20:45.046
Cece insisted.

403
00:20:45.914 --> 00:20:47.949
-She's so sweet.
-Yeah.

404
00:20:50.152 --> 00:20:53.088
(WHY IS SHE STILL HERE?
BY RENEE RAPP PLAYING)

405
00:20:56.992 --> 00:20:59.361
♪ <i>You can tell me</i> ♪

406
00:20:59.394 --> 00:21:01.196
♪ <i>You don't love her</i> ♪

407
00:21:01.229 --> 00:21:04.499
♪ <i>But you should</i>
<i>probably tell her too</i> ♪

408
00:21:04.533 --> 00:21:05.634
♪ <i>'Cause I can't keep...</i> ♪

409
00:21:05.666 --> 00:21:06.935
(GASPS)

410
00:21:07.435 --> 00:21:08.669
No. no. no.

411
00:21:08.702 --> 00:21:11.039
Absolutely fucking not!

412
00:21:12.073 --> 00:21:13.108
Oh. my God.

413
00:21:21.815 --> 00:21:24.019
I want you to feel safe here.

414
00:21:26.087 --> 00:21:27.122
I do.

415
00:21:29.890 --> 00:21:31.792
For your door. as requested.

416
00:21:32.327 --> 00:21:33.861
Thanks.

417
00:21:37.465 --> 00:21:39.800
So how was last night?
With Andrew?

418
00:21:41.236 --> 00:21:42.703
Good.

419
00:21:42.736 --> 00:21:44.372
I made chicken piccata.

420
00:21:45.574 --> 00:21:47.375
He's a dream. isn't he?

421
00:21:48.876 --> 00:21:50.679
He pretends to like everything
I make him.

422
00:21:50.711 --> 00:21:51.947
even if he hates it.

423
00:21:57.485 --> 00:21:58.752
Mmm.

424
00:22:01.456 --> 00:22:03.425
That's a lot of bacon. Millie.

425
00:22:03.458 --> 00:22:05.160
Are you trying to kill us?

426
00:22:10.764 --> 00:22:12.133
Where are you going?

427
00:22:14.402 --> 00:22:15.604
I have...

428
00:22:15.637 --> 00:22:16.938
Saturday off.

429
00:22:16.972 --> 00:22:18.073
Isn't that
what we talked about?

430
00:22:18.106 --> 00:22:21.109
No. I...
I can't spare you today.

431
00:22:21.977 --> 00:22:24.012
I missed
my hair salon appointment

432
00:22:24.045 --> 00:22:27.482
because you threw away
my notes. (CHUCKLES)

433
00:22:27.515 --> 00:22:29.117
Remember?

434
00:22:29.150 --> 00:22:32.220
I have a meeting
that I can't miss.

435
00:22:32.254 --> 00:22:33.521
(SCOFFS)

436
00:22:33.555 --> 00:22:34.923
You have a meeting?

437
00:22:35.490 --> 00:22:36.925
What's the meeting for?

438
00:22:39.760 --> 00:22:41.396
If I could just have
a couple hours off.

439
00:22:41.429 --> 00:22:42.464
and then I'll come back.

440
00:22:42.497 --> 00:22:44.798
Millie. absolutely not.

441
00:22:44.832 --> 00:22:46.635
-ANDREW: Baby?
-I can't have you... What?

442
00:22:46.668 --> 00:22:48.903
Sweetheart. it's okay.
She can go.

443
00:22:50.405 --> 00:22:52.507
-But. Andy. it's your day off.
-I know. exactly.

444
00:22:52.540 --> 00:22:55.977
And that's why we're gonna go
to the park... fly this kite.

445
00:22:56.011 --> 00:22:57.145
And we've been waiting
all week to fly. right?

446
00:22:57.178 --> 00:22:58.113
We're doing donuts.
we're doing kites.

447
00:22:58.146 --> 00:22:59.847
and then we're doing ballet.

448
00:23:01.416 --> 00:23:02.450
Go. Take your time.

449
00:23:06.421 --> 00:23:08.556
-Bye. Mama.
-Bye. baby.

450
00:23:10.791 --> 00:23:14.062
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

451
00:23:14.095 --> 00:23:15.230
Have fun.

452
00:23:19.734 --> 00:23:21.002
Thanks.

453
00:23:23.338 --> 00:23:24.439
(DOOR OPENS)

454
00:23:26.408 --> 00:23:27.841
PAM: Hey. how are you doin'?

455
00:23:27.875 --> 00:23:29.611
MILLIE: I'm good.

456
00:23:29.644 --> 00:23:31.046
Still writing in your journal?

457
00:23:31.079 --> 00:23:34.015
Uh. yeah.
Do you wanna read it?

458
00:23:34.049 --> 00:23:34.949
God. no.

459
00:23:34.983 --> 00:23:37.719
I have enough shit
to read as it is.

460
00:23:37.752 --> 00:23:40.055
So you left the job
at Charlie's?

461
00:23:40.088 --> 00:23:43.857
Well. this housekeeping job
just sort of fell into my lap.

462
00:23:43.891 --> 00:23:46.428
And it's live-in.
so I'm saving a fortune on rent.

463
00:23:46.461 --> 00:23:48.496
Okay. that's good.

464
00:23:48.530 --> 00:23:51.399
I have my new address here.

465
00:23:51.433 --> 00:23:52.967
and phone number.

466
00:23:53.001 --> 00:23:55.437
The family is really amazing.

467
00:23:55.470 --> 00:23:56.938
I feel... I feel lucky.

468
00:23:56.971 --> 00:23:59.174
Must make meeting new people
a little tough. though.

469
00:23:59.207 --> 00:24:00.775
having to live with a family.

470
00:24:00.809 --> 00:24:02.177
I mean. you would
think that. right?

471
00:24:02.210 --> 00:24:06.181
But I have already met
a ton of really cool nannies.

472
00:24:06.214 --> 00:24:08.016
Any mannies in there?
(CHUCKLES)

473
00:24:08.917 --> 00:24:11.786
Are you asking me
about my love life. Pam?

474
00:24:11.820 --> 00:24:13.188
If I know how Tinder works.

475
00:24:13.221 --> 00:24:16.024
or if I'm horn dogging
all over Great Neck

476
00:24:16.057 --> 00:24:17.392
because I haven't gotten laid
in ten years?

477
00:24:17.425 --> 00:24:20.295
No. I'm just saying
human connections are important.

478
00:24:21.663 --> 00:24:22.931
Definitely.

479
00:24:22.964 --> 00:24:25.066
But hold onto this job.
Millie.

480
00:24:25.767 --> 00:24:27.168
And the living situation.

481
00:24:29.104 --> 00:24:31.306
You'll need both.
or you'll be back at Bedford

482
00:24:31.339 --> 00:24:34.743
serving the five years
left on your sentence.

483
00:24:34.776 --> 00:24:36.978
And I don't like that for you.

484
00:24:37.011 --> 00:24:39.180
I don't like that
for me. either.

485
00:24:42.016 --> 00:24:44.619
(PHONE VIBRATING)

486
00:24:48.022 --> 00:24:49.824
-Hi. Nina. I'm just--
<i>-I need you to pick up Cece</i>

487
00:24:49.858 --> 00:24:52.761
<i>from ballet class. 1:45.</i>
<i>and don't be late.</i>

488
00:24:52.794 --> 00:24:53.995
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

489
00:24:54.028 --> 00:24:57.031
Um. okay. where is it? Nina?

490
00:24:58.666 --> 00:25:00.001
What?

491
00:25:01.369 --> 00:25:02.604
Ballet school?

492
00:25:03.037 --> 00:25:04.272
Ballet class.

493
00:25:06.274 --> 00:25:07.709
Little kids.

494
00:25:07.742 --> 00:25:09.477
Fuck.

495
00:25:09.511 --> 00:25:10.879
INSTRUCTOR: Tendu right.

496
00:25:10.912 --> 00:25:14.382
And curtsy
and open to the left.

497
00:25:14.416 --> 00:25:15.717
Foot behind you.

498
00:25:15.750 --> 00:25:18.253
Excellent. and close to first.

499
00:25:18.286 --> 00:25:20.188
Fabulous class today.
Thank you.

500
00:25:20.221 --> 00:25:22.323
Let's go get
our bags and shoes.

